fr.upmc.datacenter.hardware.processors

Class ProcessorDynamicState

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.upmc.datacenter.hardware.processors.ProcessorDynamicState
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    fr.upmc.components.interfaces.DataOfferedI.DataI, fr.upmc.components.interfaces.DataRequiredI.DataI, ProcessorDynamicStateI, TimeStampingI, java.io.Serializable

    public class ProcessorDynamicState
extends java.lang.Object
implements ProcessorDynamicStateI
    The class ProcessorDynamicState implements objects representing a snapshot of the dynamic state of a processor component to be pulled or pushed through the dynamic state data interface.

    Description

    Invariant

     invariant              timestamp >= 0 && timestamperIP != null
 invariant              coresIdleStatus != null && currentCoreFrequencies != null
